**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

*Figure 167. Hyphenation*

With the help of hyphenation, texts can be automatically (orthographically correct) separated. This is especially useful when using *Justify*.

## Preparations
The library for hyphenation cannot be delivered directly with the *Doxee Template Designer*, due to licensing reasons. The file *fop-hyph.jar *can be downloaded from the following website: [http://offo.sourceforge.net/](http://offo.sourceforge.net/)

Afterwards it has to be copied to the directory *&lt;Infinica Template Designer installation directory&gt;/plugins/com.infinica.plugins.documentrendering*&lt;Version&gt;/lib and the *Doxee Template Designer *must be restarted.

## Allocation of the language in the document
As hyphenation is language- and country-specific, an appropriate language code must be (as it is for the spelling) assigned to the text.

The appropriate language option (group Hyphenation) is located under Properties &gt; Advanced. As hyphenation may differ despite the same language in different countries (e.g. US and UK) the field country must be filled accordingly as well.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 168. assign language code to the text*

The language can be used on the Page Sequence, as well as on block-level. If the template is written in one language, a sole assignment of the attribute language on the *Page Sequence *suffices. Differing blocks can be overwritten by assigning different values.

## Activation of the hyphenation
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

*Figure 169. activation of the hyphenation*

Hyphenation can be activated on the Page Sequence, then it will be activated for all containing elements. Since hyphenation is not always useful, it can be deactivated at block- level with the attribute *hyphenate=false *(group *Hyphenation*).
